  • Method Details

    • getMazeFromIHM

      public final Maze getMazeFromIHM() throws MazeReadingException
      getMazeFromIhm : generates a maze (from the class maze) from the boxesPanel : it basically gets the MBoxPanel and convert them into a maze (which are MBox)
      Returns:
      Maze : a maze (height, width and MBox[][]) that is created from the IHM
      Throws:
      MazeReadingException

    • exportMaze

      public final void exportMaze() throws MazeReadingException
      exportMaze : once the button export maze is clicked, we can export a maze. It's up to the player to decide what is the name of the File exported, but it's located in the folder data
      Throws:
      MazeReadingException

    • importMaze

      public final void importMaze() throws MazeReadingException, IOException, FileNotFoundException
      importMaze : once the button export maze is clicked, we can import a maze. It's up to the player to decide what is the name of the File he wants to import, but the file has to be located in the folder data
      Throws:
      MazeReadingException
      IOException
      FileNotFoundException

    • rebootMaze

      public final void rebootMaze()
      rebootMaze : once the button Reboot Maze is clicked, we have to clear the mBoxesPanel. this method just converts every MBoxPanel (Wall, Path..) into an EmptyBox

    • solveMaze

      public final void solveMaze() throws MazeReadingException, IOException
      solveMaze : once the button Solve Maze is clicked, we have to print on screen the solution this method just converts gets the maze from the IHM, uses the Dijkstra method to solve it and print the solution
      Throws:
      MazeReadingException
      IOException
